May met with Congressional Republicans at their biannual joint retreat in Philadelphia, on 26 January. May addressed both the [[Republican Conference of the United States House of Representatives|House Republican Conference]] and the [[Republican Conference of the United States Senate|Senate Republican Conference]], where she called on U.S. lawmakers not to renounce the [[Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action|Iran nuclear deal]] and to support [[international organization]]s like [[NATO]] and the [[United Nations]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wells|first1=Matt|last2=Almasy|first2=Steve|title=British PM May: Praise for Trump -- but strong words, too|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/01/26/politics/theresa-may-us-speech/|accessdate=27 January 2017|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=27 January 2017}}</ref> Following this, May travelled to Washington, D.C. to meet with [[President of the United States|President]] [[Donald Trump]] at the [[White House]]. She was the first head of government to meet with Trump since his [[Inauguration of Donald Trump|inauguration]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Khan|first1=Shehab|title=Theresa May to meet Donald Trump on Friday, White House officials confirm|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/donald-trump-theresa-may-meeting-this-week-president-a7539586.html#gallery|accessdate=22 January 2017|work=[[The Independent]]|date=22 January 2017}}</ref> The two leaders discussed [[United Kingdom–United States relations#Trade, investment and the economy|trade relations]] ahead of the Brexit negotiations, NATO, the Syrian Civil War, relations with Russia, and [[counter-terrorism]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dewan|first1=Angela|last2=Deaton|first2=Jennifer|title=Britain's Prime Minister May to visit Trump in Washington|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/01/22/europe/may-trump-uk-us-visit/index.html|accessdate=23 January 2017|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=23 January 2017}}</ref> May also laid a wreath at the [[Tomb of the Unknowns]] at [[Arlington National Cemetery]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Allen|first1=Nick|last2=Hope|first2=Christopher|title=Theresa May lays wreath at Arlington cemetery ahead of meeting with Donald Trump to discuss new trade deal and defence|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/27/theresa-may-meets-donald-trump-white-house-live/|accessdate=27 January 2017|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=27 January 2017}}</ref>
