| {{flagu|United States}} 
| [[New York City]] 
| {{sort|2017-09-19|19–20 September}}
| May travelled from Canada to New York to attend the [[United Nations General Assembly|UN General Assembly]] alongside the British foreign secretary, [[Boris Johnson]], though it was later announced that Johnson's separate UN meeting was cancelled and that he would fly back with May.<ref>http://www.clactonandfrintongazette.co.uk/news/national/15547309.Where___s_the_emergency_Brexit__PM_and_Boris_share_plane_home_from_UN_gathering/</ref> It will be the second speech May makes to the UN.  After arriving in New York, May held a press conference about Brexit and her relationship with Johnson<ref>https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-theresa-may-speech-latest-florence-boris-johnson-rebellion-contribution-a7955961.html</ref> and also held a special meeting with President Trump's daughter [[Ivanka Trump|Ivanka]] and United Nations Secretary General [[Antonio Guterres]].<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/09/20/ivanka-trump-praises-theresa-may-meet-new-york/</ref>  

On September 20, May held a bilateral meeting  on the sidelines of the UN General Assembly with Iranian President [[Hassan Rouhani]] and Rouhani announced that Iran was ready to expand ties to Britain in all fields,<ref name=iranmay>http://ifpnews.com/exclusive/iran-uk-expansion-bilateral-ties/</ref> citing Britain's support of the [[Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action]].<ref name=iranmay />  She also attended a major UN Security Council meeting which saw the passage of a UN resolution on peacekeeping reforms and met with US Vice President [[Mike Pence]].<ref>https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/africa/pence-applauds-un-resolution-on-peacekeeping-reform/2017/09/20/1f13bcdc-9e2f-11e7-b2a7-bc70b6f98089_story.html</ref>  May would later address the [[United Nations General Assembly|UN General Assembly]] and warned tech firms to go "further and faster" in removing extremist content promoting terrorism,<ref>https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41327816</ref> as well as other issues.<ref>https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/politics/trump-theresa-may-paris-agreement-criticism-climate-deal-un-speech-a7958096.html</ref><ref>http://www.express.co.uk/news/world/856711/theresa-may-united-nations-millions-withhold-terrorism-bureaucracy</ref>  She also met with US President [[Donald Trump]] on the General Assembly sidelines to discuss trade, security, defense and foreign relations between Britain and the United States of America.<ref>http://www.sfchronicle.com/news/politics/article/The-Latest-Kerry-charges-Trump-speech-to-UN-was-12214303.php</ref><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d7kdI0tCnV4</ref>
