|-
| {{Flag|Italy}}
| [[Lake Garda]]
| {{sort|2018-07-28|28 July – 2 August}}
| May went on her Summer Break.
|-
| {{Flag|France}}
| [[Fort de Bregancon]]
| {{sort|2018-08-02|2–3 August}}
| May met with French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] to discuss progression on the Brexit talks.
|-
| {{Flag|France}}
| [[Amiens]]
| {{sort|2018-08-08|8 August}}
| May attended commemoration services marking the Centenary of the [[Battle of Amiens (1918)|Battle of Amiens]] which occurred during [[World War I]].
|-
| {{Flag|South Africa}}
| [[Cape Town]]
| {{sort|2018-08-28|28 August}}
| May gave a keynote speech on trade and how UK private sector investment can be brought into Africa.  She also had a bilateral meeting with South African President [[Cyril Ramaphosa]], she also visited Robben Island, where Nelson Mandela was imprisoned.
|-
| {{Flag|Nigeria}}
| [[Lagos]]
| {{sort|2018-08-29|29 August}}
| May met with the Nigerian government to discuss bilateral trade talks and strengthening the bond between the two countries.
|-
| {{Flag|Kenya}}
| [[Nairobi]]
| {{sort|2018-08-30|30 August}}
| May met with [[President of Kenya|President]] [[Uhuru Kenyatta]] for talks on bilateral trade and announced plans to open a cyber security centre in Nairobi to combat human trafficking.
|-
| {{Flag|Austria}}
| [[Salzburg]]
| {{sort|2018-09-19|19–20 September}}
| Attended a working summit with EU leaders. Many of them had rejected the Chequers Brexit Plan.
|-
